Conclusions:

Heading measurement goes from 0-360 degrees succesfully while the robot remains still, and it remains constant
with a +/- 5 degree error

Gyro readings remain the same +/- 0.01 throughout readings

Accelerometer readings remain the same +/- 0.1 throughout readings

Autorange does not affect the readings when the robot remains still
